 cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","1 celery stalk (approx. 50 g), cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","1 brown onion (approx. 100 g), cut into quarters","1 garlic clove","20 g extra virgin olive oil","60 g dry white wine","500 g water","2 tsp vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","1 pinch sea salt, to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, to taste","400 g blade roast beef, cut or trussed into a square shape"]},{"title":"Seeded mustard sauce","content":["30 g butter, softened","1 pinch salt, to taste","1 pinch freshly ground black pepper, to taste","1 tbsp plain flour","2 tsp wholegrain mustard","70 g milk"]},{"title":"Carrot, pumpkin and ginger purée","content":["1 - 2 cm cube fresh ginger, peeled","½ orange, zest only, no white pith","50 g brown onion, cut into halves","150 g pumpkin, peeled and cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","150 g carrot, peeled and cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","80 g water","½ tsp chicken stock paste (see Tips)","100 g fresh green beans, ends trimmed","20 g unsalted butter","1 - 2 pinches salt, to taste","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper, to taste"]}],"id":"r78477","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-LnBiYluqQEI\/XZQxJGJVBAI\/AAAAAAAAcsQ\/L2NkkQ4r6xAPrtYhLJGHruNTUvrNrNhOACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mpqm07-b9YkUrO98.png","title":"Pocket roast beef with seeded mustard sauce","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"70.5 g","fat":"36 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"22 g","calories":"2986 kJ \/ 711 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, large jug, serving jug","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the<em> Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste and Chicken stock paste recipes.","Ask your butcher to prepare your blade roast, as it can be hard to purchase a 400 g roast. Another option is to purchase an 800-900 g blade roast and cut it into halves. Freeze the other half for another day.","For optimum cooking, make sure your roast weighs no more than 450 g and that the measuring cup fits easily in the mixing bowl lid. Your roast should not obstruct the hole in mixing bowl lid.","You may like to brown your blade roast in a hot frying pan just before serving for a little added colour.","Cooking time for the roast will depend on the size and weight of the meat.","If you would like more vegetables with your roast, steam vegetables in the Varoma while the meat is cooking in step 2. Vegetable cooking times will vary.","Leftover beef stock and vegetables can be used as a base for soup the next day."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 30m","2 portions"]}